doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    title Privacy Policy | Flora
    meta(charset="utf-8")
    meta(name="viewport", content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1")
    link(rel="stylesheet", href="/stylesheets/flora.css")
  body
    div.legal-container
      h1 Flora Privacy Policy
      p Last Updated: Mar 30, 2026
      
      p Welcome to Flora. We are a community-focused platform dedicated to connecting vegans and those who respect the vegan way of life through dating, friendships, and local events.
      p We believe that privacy is a fundamental right. This policy outlines exactly what information we collect, why we need it, and how we protect it.
      
      h2 1. Information We Collect
      p To operate the Flora platform and keep our community safe, we collect the following types of information:
      ul
        li #[strong Account & Profile Information:] When you create an account, we collect your email address, legal name (for verification), and the profile details you choose to share (such as your display name, pronouns, gender identity, relationship goals, and vegan journey).
        li #[strong Media and Voice Notes:] We only collect the specific photos and voice notes you explicitly choose to upload to your profile. We do not request or require access to your entire camera roll or media library.
        li #[strong Location Data:] Flora does not track, collect, or store your precise GPS coordinates. We only collect your city and zip code to show you relevant local profiles and events.
        li #[strong Communication Data:] We securely store the messages you send to your matches and your RSVP statuses for community events.
        li #[strong Swipe and Activity Data:] We log your interactions, such as profiles you have liked, passed on, or reported, to manage your matches and Discover feed.
        
      h2 2. Identity Verification
      p To maintain a safe environment, all users must be 21 or older and pass an ID verification check.
      ul
        li #[strong Third-Party Processing:] We partner with a secure third-party provider, Didit, to process your government-issued ID.
        li #[strong Zero Local Storage:] Flora does not store, host, or retain copies of your legal ID documents or biometric data on our servers. We only receive a secure confirmation of your age and verification status.
        
      h2 3. How We Use Your Information
      p We use your data strictly to provide and improve the Flora experience.
      ul
        li #[strong Matching and Discovery:] To show your profile to compatible users in your city and display relevant local events.
        li #[strong Safety and Moderation:] To enforce our zero-tolerance policy against harassment. We use your data to investigate reports, block malicious users, and suspend accounts that violate our Terms of Service.
        li #[strong Platform Operations:] To process your premium membership subscriptions, send you push notifications for new matches or messages, and resolve support tickets.
        
      h2 4. How We Share Your Information
      p Flora does not and will never sell your personal data to third parties. We only share your information with the trusted infrastructure partners required to run the app:
      ul
        li #[strong Cloud Infrastructure:] Your profile text and app data are securely hosted using Firebase (Google Cloud) and Turso databases.
        li #[strong Media Hosting:] The photos and voice notes you upload are securely stored using Cloudflare R2 buckets.
        li #[strong Safety Services:] Profile images may be temporarily processed by Google Cloud Vision API during upload to automatically detect and block inappropriate or explicit content before it reaches the community.
        li #[strong Legal Compliance:] We may disclose your information if required by law, such as in response to a subpoena, or to protect the safety of our users and the public (e.g., escalating severe threats to law enforcement).
        
      h2 5. Data Retention and Deletion
      p You have total control over your presence on Flora.
      ul
        li #[strong Account Deletion:] You can delete your account at any time through the app settings. Deleting your account will permanently erase your profile, photos, and chat history from our active databases.
        li #[strong Soft Deletion for Events:] If you host an event and decide to delete it, it is immediately removed from all public feeds, though a record may remain in our database for safety and moderation purposes.
        li #[strong Banned Users:] If an account is banned for violating our Terms of Service, we retain basic identifiers (such as the email address and Didit verification status) to prevent the user from creating a new account.
        
      h2 6. Your Rights
      p Depending on where you live (such as California), you may have specific rights regarding your personal data, including:
      ul
        li The right to know what personal data we collect.
        li The right to request the deletion of your personal data.
        li The right to correct inaccurate information on your profile.
      p To exercise any of these rights, or if you have any questions about this policy, please reach out to us.
      
      h2 7. Contact Us
      p If you have questions, concerns, or feedback regarding your privacy on Flora, please contact our management team:
      p 
        a(href="mailto:eporiamusic@gmail.com") Email: eporiamusic@gmail.com
